{{Quote|Quoreal was the Supreme Overlord before Shimrra. Many do not think the gods chose Shimrra to take his place, they believe that Shimrra dishonorably murdered him. Quoreal's old followers are understandably a reticent group, but they still exist.|[[Harrar]]|<ref name="The New Jedi Order: The Final Prophecy">''[[The New Jedi Order: The Final Prophecy]]''</ref>}}
'''Quorealists''' were [[Yuuzhan Vong]] that believed [[Supreme Overlord]] [[Quoreal]] was right in not wanting to invade [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] and opposed [[Shimrra Jamaane]]'s [[Jamaane coup|ascension]] as Supreme Overlord of the Yuuzhan Vong. They believed that Quoreal and his [[Priest caste|Priests]] were right about [[Zonama Sekot/Legends|Zonama Sekot]] being able to destroy the Yuuzhan Vong. When Shimrra erased knowledge of the living world's discovery, the Quorealists were among the few who kepts records of its existence.

When the [[Yuuzhan Vong War|invasion]] began with many victories, the Quorealists ceased their concerns, believing that Shimrra may have been right in overthrowning Quoreal. However, as the [[Jeedai heresy]] spread, and the [[World Brain]] continued to sabotage the [[Terraforming/Legends|Vongforming]] of [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] into [[Coruscant/Legends#Yuuzhan'tar|Yuuzhan'tar]], the Quorealists again became vocal.

[[Drathul]], as [[High Prefect]] of the [[Intendant caste]], was the highest ranking known Quorealist among the [[Elite (Yuuzhan Vong)|Elite]]. [[Harrar]] may also have been a Quorealist. [[Czulkang Lah]], former [[Warmaster]] and close acquiantance of Harrar, had also expressed opposition to invading the Galaxy, but it is unknown if he sided with the Quorealists.

